{
  "texts": [
    "Advanced methods, such as TrojanPuzzule [5], rely on carefully crafted triggers for success.",
    "Arbitrarily designed triggers may not be able to activate backdoors.",
    "Additionally, some attacks, such as AgentPoison [34], are based on assumptions that the attacker has black-box access to the models.",
    "Such assumptions may not be realistic in realworld scenarios.",
    "Furthermore, several methods, e.g., NightShade [229] and AutoPoision [240], were evaluated on LMs or small-scale LLMs."
  ]
}